---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Home" description="Kim Lab at Rosalind Franklin University - Research on ion channels, neuronal function, and alcohol toxicity using C. elegans">

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Welcome to the Kim Lab</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">Investigating the molecular mechanisms of neuronal function and disease</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>About Our Research</h2>
      <p>
        Our laboratory uses <em>Caenorhabditis elegans</em> as a model organism to investigate genes
        essential for movement control. Through genetic and genomic approaches, we aim to understand
        the mechanisms underlying neurological and neuromuscular diseases.
      </p>

      <div class="highlight">
        <p>
          <strong>Our Mission:</strong> To advance understanding of ion channel function, synaptic
          transmission, and the molecular basis of alcohol-related disorders through innovative
          research using <em>C. elegans</em> as a powerful genetic model system.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Research Focus Areas</h2>

      <div class="grid grid-3">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Ion Channel Localization</h3>
          <p>
            We investigate how ion channels are transported to and cluster at specific cellular
            locations, with particular emphasis on CaV2 voltage-gated calcium channels and their
            role in synaptic transmission.
          </p>
          <a href="/kimlab-website/research/" class="btn">Learn More</a>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h3>BK Channel Function</h3>
          <p>
            Our work examines the SLO-1 calcium-activated potassium channel's relationship to
            alcohol intoxication and tolerance, revealing how channel clustering affects acute
            alcohol responses.
          </p>
          <a href="/kimlab-website/research/" class="btn">Learn More</a>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h3>Alcohol Toxicity</h3>
          <p>
            We study the chronic effects of alcohol on neurological function, with a focus on
            mitochondria as the primary cellular target and protective stress response mechanisms.
          </p>
          <a href="/kimlab-website/research/" class="btn">Learn More</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Why <em>C. elegans</em>?</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-2">
        <div>
          <p>
            <em>Caenorhabditis elegans</em> is a powerful model organism for studying the nervous
            system. With only 302 neurons and a completely mapped connectome, it provides an
            unparalleled opportunity to understand neural circuits at the cellular and molecular level.
          </p>
          <p>
            The genetic tools available in <em>C. elegans</em> allow us to precisely manipulate
            gene function and observe the effects on behavior, providing direct insights into
            the mechanisms of neurological diseases.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-features">
          <ul>
            <li><strong>302 neurons</strong> with fully mapped connections</li>
            <li><strong>Transparent body</strong> for live imaging</li>
            <li><strong>Short generation time</strong> (3 days)</li>
            <li><strong>Powerful genetics</strong> for gene manipulation</li>
            <li><strong>Conserved genes</strong> relevant to human disease</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section cta-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Join Our Team</h2>
      <p>
        We are always looking for motivated students and researchers interested in neuroscience,
        genetics, and cell biology.
      </p>
      <a href="/kimlab-website/contact/" class="btn">Contact Us</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .hero {
    background: url('/kimlab-website/banner.jpg');
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: center;
    color: white;
    padding: 8rem 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    color: #1a202c;
    font-size: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    text-shadow: 1px 1px 2px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
  }

  .hero-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    color: #2d3748;
    text-shadow: 1px 1px 2px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
  }

  .model-features {
    background-color: var(--bg-alt);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .model-features ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .model-features li {
    padding: 0.75rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  }

  .model-features li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .cta-section {
    text-align: center;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--bg-alt) 0%, #e2e8f0 100%);
  }

  .cta-section h2 {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .hero-subtitle {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }
  }
</style>
